  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "## Deep Audit V2: hx-visually-hidden\n\n**Comprehensive enterprise-grade quality audit** of the `hx-visually-hidden` utility component.\n\n### Audit Dimensions\n1. **Design Tokens** — Verify CSS approach uses standard visually-hidden technique (not display:none).\n2. **Accessibility** — This IS the accessibility utility. Verify it works correctly for screen readers in all contexts.\n3. **Functionality** — Content hidden visually but available to assistive technology. Focusable variant if needed.\n4. **TypeScript** — Strict mode. No `any`. Proper types.\n5. **CSS Architecture** — Shadow DOM encapsulation. Standard visually-hidden CSS pattern.\n6. **CEM Accuracy** — `custom-elements.json` matches actual public API exactly.\n7. **Test Coverage** — Vitest browser tests. Verify screen reader behavior.\n8. **Storybook** — Stories demonstrating usage with screen reader context.\n9. **Drupal Compatibility** — Works in Twig templates without modification.\n10. **Portability** — No framework dependencies. Works in vanilla HTML.\n\n### wc-mcp Tool Usage (MANDATORY)\nUse these MCP tools during your audit:\n- `score_component({ tagName: \"hx-visually-hidden\" })` — Get health score baseline\n- `get_component({ tagName: \"hx-visually-hidden\" })` — Full component details\n- `analyze_accessibility({ tagName: \"hx-visually-hidden\" })` — A11Y audit\n- `list_css_parts({ tagName: \"hx-visually-hidden\" })` — CSS Parts inventory\n- `list_slots({ tagName: \"hx-visually-hidden\" })` — Slots inventory\n\nIf any wc-mcp tool returns unexpected results or errors, report the bug to the wc-tools board at `/Volumes/Development/booked/wc-tools`.\n\n### Deliverables\n- Fix all issues found inline\n- Update tests to cover gaps\n- Update Storybook stories if needed\n- Ensure CEM is accurate after changes\n- Run `npm run verify` before committing",
